ionship\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-3 text-lg text-[#d4af37]/70 font-serif italic\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"And you don't even know it.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-6 flex items-center gap-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[#d4af37]/20 border border-[#d4af37]/30 flex items-center justify-center\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-bold text-[#d4af37] font-serif\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"H\\\"}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-semibold text-white font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hakeem Lesolang\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-[#718096] font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hypnotherapist \\u0026 Peak Performance Coach\\\"}]]}]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-16 h-px bg-[#d4af37]/30 mb-12\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-custom\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"That argument last Tuesday wasn't about the dishes. It was about two dysregulated nervous systems trying to find safety in a room that suddenly felt dangerous.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"2\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Let me explain.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"4\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Polyvagal Truth Nobody Told You\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"6\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Dr. Stephen Porges gave us polyvagal theory, and it fundamentally rewired how I understand couples. Here's the short version: your autonomic nervous system has three states — ventral vagal (safe, connected, present), sympathetic (fight or flight), and dorsal vagal (shutdown, collapse, dissociation).\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"8\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"When you're in ventral vagal, you can listen. You can be curious. You can hear your partner say \\\\\\\"I felt abandoned when you didn't call\\\\\\\" and respond with warmth instead of defense. But here's what most couples don't realise — \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eyou cannot access empathy from a dysregulated state.\\u003c/strong\\u003e It's not a character flaw. It's neurobiology.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"10\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"When your sympathetic nervous system fires — heart rate climbing past 100bpm, jaw tightening, breath shortening — your prefrontal cortex goes offline. The part of your brain responsible for perspective-taking, emotional regulation, and compassionate listening literally shuts down. You are now operating from the amygdala. And the amygdala has one question: \\u003cem class=\\\\\\\"text-[#d4af37]/80\\\\\\\"\\u003eAm I safe?\\u003c/em\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"12\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The 20-Minute Rule That Saves Marriages\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"14\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"John Gottman's research at the Love Lab in Seattle found that once a partner's heart rate exceeds 100 beats per minute during conflict, they become physiologically incapable of productive conversation. He calls it \\\\\\\"diffuse physiological arousal\\\\\\\" (DPA). I call it the moment your body hijacks your relationship.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"16\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The intervention? Twenty minutes. That's how long it takes for cortisol and adrenaline to clear your bloodstream enough to re-engage the prefrontal cortex. Not five minutes of stewing in the bathroom. Not ten minutes of rehearsing your rebuttal. Twenty minutes of genuine physiological downregulation — slow breathing, bilateral stimulation, cold water on your wrists.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"18\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Most couples I work with resist this. \\\\\\\"If I walk away, she'll think I don't care.\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"If I take a break, he'll use it to shut down.\\\\\\\" I hear you. But here's the neuroscience: \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eyou are not walking away from your partner. You are walking toward your capacity to actually be present for them.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"20\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"What Hypnotherapy Reveals About Couple Conflict\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"22\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In my hypnotherapy practice, I regularly take clients into trance states where we can access the subconscious patterning beneath their conflict cycles. What we almost always find is that the \\\\\\\"trigger\\\\\\\" in the relationship is rarely about the relationship at all.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"24\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"It's about a seven-year-old who learned that raised voices meant danger. It's about a teenager who discovered that silence was the only safe response to an unpredictable parent. It's about a young adult who figured out that if you never need anything, nobody can disappoint you.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"26\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"These patterns don't disappear because you're thirty-five and in love. They go underground. They become your attachment style, your conflict strategy, your definition of \\\\\\\"normal.\\\\\\\" And they run your relationship like invisible software — until you make them conscious.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"28\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The NLP Reframe That Changes Everything\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"30\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Here's a reframe I use with every couple: \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eyour partner is not the enemy. Their nervous system is not the enemy. The pattern is the enemy.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"32\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In NLP, we talk about the map versus the territory. Your partner's map of reality — shaped by their neurology, their history, their subconscious programming — is different from yours. When they react in a way that feels disproportionate, irrational, or hurtful, they are not responding to \\u003cem class=\\\\\\\"text-[#d4af37]/80\\\\\\\"\\u003eyou.\\u003c/em\\u003e They are responding to their map's interpretation of you. And that map was drawn long before you entered the picture.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"34\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"This doesn't excuse harmful behaviour. It does, however, open a door. Because once you stop taking your partner's dysregulation personally and start getting curious about the map they're operating from, conflict transforms from a battlefield into a classroom.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"36\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Practice\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"38\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Tonight, try this: when you feel the first flicker of activation — the tightened chest, the urge to defend, the impulse to withdraw — pause. Place one hand on your chest. Take five breaths where your exhale is longer than your inhle. Say to yourself: \\u003cem class=\\\\\\\"text-[#d4af37]/80\\\\\\\"\\u003eThis is my nervous system trying to protect me. I am safe. My partner is not the threat.\\u003c/em\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"40\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Then re-engage.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"42\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"It won't be perfect. It doesn't have to be. But you'll be doing something radical — you'll be choosing your relationship over your reactivity. And that, right there, is the uncommon practice.\\\"}}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-16 rounded-2xl border border-[#d4af37]/30 bg-gradient-to-b from-[#d4af37]/10 to-transparent p-8 text-center\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h3\\\",null,{\\\